findings.recommendation:
Before pushing error.message into notes[], scrub URLs with a simple regex: replace /https?:\/\/[^\s]*/g with '<rpc-url>' (or just '<rpc>' if even the host is sensitive). Alternatively redact only the path component to preserve the host for diagnostics. Pattern:
  const safeMessage = message.replace(/https?:\/\/\S+/g, '<rpc-url>');
  notes.push(`authorizationState: ambiguous probe outcome — ${safeMessage}`);

Apply the same URL-scrub regex to the error message before printing:
  const safeMsg = message.replace(/https?:\/\/\S+/g, '<rpc-url>');
  console.error(`[verify-usdc-eip3009] RPC unavailable or USDC reverted view call: ${safeMsg}`);

Optional for this spike: add a simple URL pre-check before createPublicClient:
  const rpcUrl = process.env.ARC_RPC_URL ?? DEFAULT_RPC_URL;
  if (!/^https?:\/\//i.test(rpcUrl)) {
    console.error('[verify-usdc-eip3009] ARC_RPC_URL must be an http/https URL');
    process.exit(1);
  }
This is a low-friction guard and makes the failure mode explicit.
